Executive Reality Check
You have 30 days, one person, and zero ad budget to generate 10,000 traction signals (stars + clones + pip installs) for an AI agent security framework that currently has 3 GitHub stars and a README-only public repo. The core product is still in a private repo.
This is not a marketing plan. This is a manufacturing operation for social proof and developer adoption. Every single day has a specific output. If you execute all 30 days, the math works.
THE PAPERCLIP LESSON
Paperclip went from 0 to 30,000+ stars in 21 days (March 2026). They didn't run ads. They shipped a working product that solved a real, felt pain, wrapped it in a provocative narrative ('your agents need an org chart, not better prompts'), and let ecosystem momentum do the rest. SupraWall's playbook borrows this architecture but adapts it for a solo founder with a security/guardrails positioning.

